4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING DEFINITIONS IN THE MONTANA
5 YOUTH COURT ACT; PROVIDING THAT A VICTIM MAY INCLUDE A CORPORATION OR OTHER ENTITY;
6 AND AMENDING SECTION 41-5-103, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 41-5-103, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "41-5-103. Definitions. As used in the Montana Youth Court Act, unless the context requires
12 otherwise, the following definitions apply:
13 (1) "Adult" means an individual who is 18 years of age or older.
14 (2) "Agency" means any entity of state or local government authorized by law to be responsible for
15 the care or rehabilitation of youth.
16 (3) "Assessment officer" means a person who is authorized by the court to provide initial intake
17 and evaluation for a youth who appears to be in need of intervention or an alleged delinquent youth.
18 (4) "Commit" means to transfer legal custody of a youth to the department or to the youth court.
19 (5) "Conditional release" means the release of a youth from a correctional facility subject to the
20 terms and conditions of the conditional release agreement provided for in 52-5-126.
21 (6) (a) "Correctional facility" means a public secure residential facility or a private secure
22 residential facility under contract with the department and operated to provide for the custody, treatment,
23 training, and rehabilitation of:
24 (i) formally adjudicated delinquent youth;
25 (ii) convicted adult offenders or criminally convicted youth; or
26 (iii) a combination of the populations described in subsections (6)(a)(i) and (6)(a)(ii) under
27 conditions set by the department in rule.
28 (b) The term does not include a state prison as defined in 53-30-101.
